This paper deals with privacy risks in machine learning models, specifically membership inference attacks. The paper discusses the vulnerability of different machine learning models and datasets to these attacks, which falls under the category of security and privacy (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper evaluates the effectiveness of different machine learning models, which falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), and data structures (cs.DS).
